ent":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":651,"cache_read_input_tokens":117347,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":651},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9","uuid":"fcfec690-76c8-4037-ac77-e2726e8ac6fa","request_id":"req_011CbxftzX47TtpKiNhDxy7w"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01L4VJWwSfSE1EamJDtS2ncW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both verdict artifacts written. Now distilling durable lessons into `.code-tips.md` (I'm its sole writer) — adding the one genuinely new rule and appending this round's provenance to the rules this round reconfirmed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":651,"cache_read_input_tokens":117347,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":651},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9","uuid":"4b4ba1c5-76ed-4ab7-a76b-ffe8d424c670","request_id":"req_011CbxftzX47TtpKiNhDxy7w"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01L4VJWwSfSE1EamJDtS2ncW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XpzTZUJRJfrc2qRg3bpcrg","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.code-tips.md","old_string":"- Tests MUST assert the POSITIVE, full observable outcome of a state\n  transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status\n  fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only\n  tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001]","new_string":"- Tests MUST assert the POSITIVE, full observable outcome of a state\n  transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status\n  fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only\n  tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001;\n  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — two gate-passing candidates asserted only\n  won/game_over and so missed leaving the wrong terminal status_message]"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":651,"cache_read_input_tokens":117347,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":651},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9","uuid":"d2f6a04a-288b-4c5d-90da-8f428f88cbf8","request_id":"req_011CbxftzX47TtpKiNhDxy7w"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XpzTZUJRJfrc2qRg3bpcrg","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.code-tips.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9","uuid":"28f6b39d-f382-49f5-b250-ac005700e6e5","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:40:49.011Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.code-tips.md","oldString":"- Tests MUST assert the POSITIVE, full observable outcome of a state\n  transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status\n  fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only\n  tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001]","newString":"- Tests MUST assert the POSITIVE, full observable outcome of a state\n  transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status\n  fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only\n  tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001;\n  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — two gate-passing candidates asserted only\n  won/game_over and so missed leaving the wrong terminal status_message]","originalFile":"# Code Tips — Word Garden 4\n\nSeeded 2026-06-12 with CROSS-PROJECT lessons distilled by prior Farnsworth\nprojects (provenance tags name the source project and task). Everything here\nis a domain-GENERAL contract — deliberately nothing Word-Garden-specific;\nproject-scoped lessons will be added by the reviewer as rounds complete.\nWorkers are read-only consumers of this file. The reviewer is its sole writer.\n\n## Testing (binds tests)\n\n- Tests MUST assert the POSITIVE, full observable outcome of a state\n  transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status\n  fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only\n  tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001]\n- Any test that touches randomness MUST inject a seeded `random.Random`;\n  never rely on global RNG state for determinism.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n- Build test fixtures by constructing the state object directly with pinned\n  values. Do NOT call a randomized constructor and then overwrite fields.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n- An end-to-end success-path test MUST force a known scenario (inject or\n  monkeypatch the source of randomness) and positively assert that the\n  success output appeared. Asserting only exit code 0, or an OR of several\n  acceptable outputs, proves nothing.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-002]\n\n## CLI contracts (binds source and tests)\n\n- argparse: NEVER wrap `parse_args` in `try/except SystemExit`. `--help` must\n  exit 0 and a usage error must exit 2; swallowing SystemExit breaks both.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002, word-garden-2 task-002]\n- Interactive input loops MUST catch `EOFError` AND `KeyboardInterrupt`,\n  print a friendly goodbye, and return 0 — never let a traceback reach the\n  user. [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002]\n- `__main__.py` MUST propagate the entry point's return code\n  (`raise SystemExit(main())` or `sys.exit(main())`).\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-002]\n\n## Design (binds source)\n\n- Strict I/O split: rendering and logic functions return strings and never\n  call `print()`/`input()`. Exactly ONE module touches stdin/stdout, and it\n  takes injectable `input_fn=input`, `output_fn=print` and uses them\n  exclusively. [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002]\n- A function accepting `rng=None` MUST default to the module-level `random`\n  functions; NEVER construct a fresh seeded `random.Random()` internally\n  (that makes production deterministic).\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001]\n- A filter/selection that yields an empty pool MUST raise `ValueError`;\n  NEVER silently fall back to the unfiltered set.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001]\n- Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every\n  other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002]\n- Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two\n  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n\n## Hygiene (binds the branch)\n\n- Never commit `__pycache__/` or `*.pyc`. Never create or write\n  `.code-tips.md` from a worker branch. Never modify `SPEC.md`,\n  `farnsworth.json`, or `tasks/`.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":12,"oldLines":7,"newStart":12,"newLines":9,"lines":["   transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status","   fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only","   tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.","-  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001]","+  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001;","+  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — two gate-passing candidates asserted only","+  won/game_over and so missed leaving the wrong terminal status_message]"," - Any test that touches randomness MUST inject a seeded `random.Random`;","   never rely on global RNG state for determinism.","   [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SzXKiE2mBqbnwcEmYGMkmv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BRbcZgss9UAGDTjkhBSANj","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.code-tips.md","old_string":"- Build test fixtures by constructing the state object directly with pinned\n  values. Do NOT call a randomized constructor and then overwrite fields.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]","new_string":"- Build test fixtures by constructing the state object directly with pinned\n  values. Do NOT call a randomized constructor (e.g. `new_game()`) and then\n  overwrite fields — that also leaks global-RNG nondeterminism into the test.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001; reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001]"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_crea