TIVE, full observable outcome of a state\n  transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status\n  fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only\n  tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001;\n  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — two gate-passing candidates asserted only\n  won/game_over and so missed leaving the wrong terminal status_message]\n- Any test that touches randomness MUST inject a seeded `random.Random`;\n  never rely on global RNG state for determinism.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n- Build test fixtures by constructing the state object directly with pinned\n  values. Do NOT call a randomized constructor and then overwrite fields.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n- An end-to-end success-path test MUST force a known scenario (inject or\n  monkeypatch the source of randomness) and positively assert that the\n  success output appeared. Asserting only exit code 0, or an OR of several\n  acceptable outputs, proves nothing.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-002]\n\n## CLI contracts (binds source and tests)\n\n- argparse: NEVER wrap `parse_args` in `try/except SystemExit`. `--help` must\n  exit 0 and a usage error must exit 2; swallowing SystemExit breaks both.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002, word-garden-2 task-002]\n- Interactive input loops MUST catch `EOFError` AND `KeyboardInterrupt`,\n  print a friendly goodbye, and return 0 — never let a traceback reach the\n  user. [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002]\n- `__main__.py` MUST propagate the entry point's return code\n  (`raise SystemExit(main())` or `sys.exit(main())`).\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-002]\n\n## Design (binds source)\n\n- Strict I/O split: rendering and logic functions return strings and never\n  call `print()`/`input()`. Exactly ONE module touches stdin/stdout, and it\n  takes injectable `input_fn=input`, `output_fn=print` and uses them\n  exclusively. [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002]\n- A function accepting `rng=None` MUST default to the module-level `random`\n  functions; NEVER construct a fresh seeded `random.Random()` internally\n  (that makes production deterministic).\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001]\n- A filter/selection that yields an empty pool MUST raise `ValueError`;\n  NEVER silently fall back to the unfiltered set.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001]\n- Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every\n  other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002]\n- Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two\n  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n\n## Hygiene (binds the branch)\n\n- Never commit `__pycache__/` or `*.pyc`. Never create or write\n  `.code-tips.md` from a worker branch. Never modify `SPEC.md`,\n  `farnsworth.json`, or `tasks/`.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":19,"oldLines":8,"newStart":19,"newLines":9,"lines":["   never rely on global RNG state for determinism.","   [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]"," - Build test fixtures by constructing the state object directly with pinned","-  values. Do NOT call a randomized constructor and then overwrite fields.","-  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]","+  values. Do NOT call a randomized constructor (e.g. `new_game()`) and then","+  overwrite fields — that also leaks global-RNG nondeterminism into the test.","+  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001; reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001]"," - An end-to-end success-path test MUST force a known scenario (inject or","   monkeypatch the source of randomness) and positively assert that the","   success output appeared. Asserting only exit code 0, or an OR of several"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01BSSfsWm5GhRMJxWpjwmZLM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01W2QAvHHoMc1yyuhhJ1kH6U","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.code-tips.md","old_string":"- Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every\n  other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002]\n- Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two\n  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]","new_string":"- Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every\n  other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002;\n  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — inline literals correlated with the weakest\n  candidates]\n- Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two\n  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge. This includes a\n  difficulty/tier set split across functions: keep the water amount and the\n  word-length band for a difficulty in ONE table, not separate dict + if/elif.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001; reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001]\n\n## Game logic (binds source and tests)\n\n- A state transition that ENDS the game (win or loss) MUST overwrite\n  `status_message` with that terminal screen's text (SPEC §6.6 win / §6.7 loss),\n  NEVER leave the ordinary correct/wrong-guess message in place. The terminal\n  message MUST name the secret word wherever the spec's end screen shows it.\n  Tests MUST assert the exact terminal message, not only `won`/`game_over`.\n  [2026-06-12, task-001]\n- `apply_guess(state, letter) -> GameState` is contracted only to RETURN the\n  updated state; implementations may mutate in place or return a fresh object.\n  Therefore callers MUST reassign (`state = apply_guess(state, letter)`) and\n  MUST NOT assume the input object is left unchanged. (binds source and tests)\n  [2026-06-12, task-001]"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":414,"cache_read_input_tokens":120143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":414},"output_tokens":50,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9","uuid":"e2df070d-7cb7-422e-a986-29c23b4e58c3","request_id":"req_011CbxfwXjKpebgrcZY7vUuW"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W2QAvHHoMc1yyuhhJ1kH6U","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.code-tips.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9","uuid":"3fccf78e-b69f-490a-bbeb-f556dfaa21bf","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:41:08.222Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.code-tips.md","oldString":"- Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every\n  other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002]\n- Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two\n  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]","newString":"- Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every\n  other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002;\n  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — inline literals correlated with the weakest\n  candidates]\n- Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two\n  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge. This includes a\n  difficulty/tier set split across functions: keep the water amount and the\n  word-length band for a difficulty in ONE table, not separate dict + if/elif.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001; reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001]\n\n## Game logic (binds source and tests)\n\n- A state transition that ENDS the game (win or loss) MUST overwrite\n  `status_message` with that terminal screen's text (SPEC §6.6 win / §6.7 loss),\n  NEVER leave the ordinary correct/wrong-guess message in place. The terminal\n  message MUST name the secret word wherever the spec's end screen shows it.\n  Tests MUST assert the exact terminal message, not only `won`/`game_over`.\n  [2026-06-12, task-001]\n- `apply_guess(state, letter) -> GameState` is contracted only to RETURN the\n  updated state; implementations may mutate in place or return a fresh object.\n  Therefore callers MUST reassign (`state = apply_guess(state, letter)`) and\n  MUST NOT assume the input object is left unchanged. (binds source and tests)\n  [2026-06-12, task-001]","originalFile":"# Code Tips — Word Garden 4\n\nSeeded 2026-06-12 with CROSS-PROJECT lessons distilled by prior Farnsworth\nprojects (provenance tags name the source project and task). Everything here\nis a domain-GENERAL contract — deliberately nothing Word-Garden-specific;\nproject-scoped lessons will be added by the reviewer as rounds complete.\nWorkers are read-only consumers of this file. The reviewer is its sole writer.\n\n## Testing (binds tests)\n\n- Tests MUST assert the POSITIVE, full observable outcome of a state\n  transition — every field that changed, including user-facing message/status\n  fields — never just boolean flags or the absence of the negative. Flag-only\n  tests have passed real bugs through the mechanical gate twice.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001, word-garden-2 task-001;\n  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — two gate-passing candidates asserted only\n  won/game_over and so missed leaving the wrong terminal status_message]\n- Any test that touches randomness MUST inject a seeded `random.Random`;\n  never rely on global RNG state for determinism.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n- Build test fixtures by constructing the state object directly with pinned\n  values. Do NOT call a randomized constructor (e.g. `new_game()`) and then\n  overwrite fields — that also leaks global-RNG nondeterminism into the test.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001; reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001]\n- An end-to-end success-path test MUST force a known scenario (inject or\n  monkeypatch the source of randomness) and positively assert that the\n  success output appeared. Asserting only exit code 0, or an OR of several\n  acceptable outputs, proves nothing.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-002]\n\n## CLI contracts (binds source and tests)\n\n- argparse: NEVER wrap `parse_args` in `try/except SystemExit`. `--help` must\n  exit 0 and a usage error must exit 2; swallowing SystemExit breaks both.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002, word-garden-2 task-002]\n- Interactive input loops MUST catch `EOFError` AND `KeyboardInterrupt`,\n  print a friendly goodbye, and return 0 — never let a traceback reach the\n  user. [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002]\n- `__main__.py` MUST propagate the entry point's return code\n  (`raise SystemExit(main())` or `sys.exit(main())`).\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-002]\n\n## Design (binds source)\n\n- Strict I/O split: rendering and logic functions return strings and never\n  call `print()`/`input()`. Exactly ONE module touches stdin/stdout, and it\n  takes injectable `input_fn=input`, `output_fn=print` and uses them\n  exclusively. [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-002]\n- A function accepting `rng=None` MUST default to the module-level `random`\n  functions; NEVER construct a fresh seeded `random.Random()` internally\n  (that makes production deterministic).\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001]\n- A filter/selection that yields an empty pool MUST raise `ValueError`;\n  NEVER silently fall back to the unfiltered set.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001]\n- Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every\n  other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002]\n- Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two\n  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n\n## Hygiene (binds the branch)\n\n- Never commit `__pycache__/` or `*.pyc`. Never create or write\n  `.code-tips.md` from a worker branch. Never modify `SPEC.md`,\n  `farnsworth.json`, or `tasks/`.\n  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":55,"oldLines":11,"newStart":55,"newLines":29,"lines":["   [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001]"," - Define user-facing message strings ONCE as module-level constants; every","   other module AND every test imports them instead of re-typing literals.","-  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002]","+  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-2 task-001 and task-002;","+  reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001 — inline literals correlated with the weakest","+  candidates]"," - Encode any configuration table (limits, bands, tiers) exactly once; two","-  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge.","-  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001]","+  copies of the same table is a bug waiting to diverge. This includes a","+  difficulty/tier set split across functions: keep the water amount and the","+  word-length band for a difficulty in ONE table, not separate dict + if/elif.","+  [seed 2026-06-12; word-garden-1 task-001; reconfirmed 2026-06-12 task-001]"," ","+## Game logic (binds source and tests)","+","+- A state transition that ENDS the game (win or loss) MUST overwrite","+  `status_message` with that terminal screen's text (SPEC §6.6 win / §6.7 loss),","+  NEVER leave the ordinary correct/wrong-guess message in place. The terminal","+  message MUST name the secret word wherever the spec's end screen shows it.","+  Tests MUST assert the exact terminal message, not only `won`/`game_over`.","+  [2026-06-12, task-001]","+- `apply_guess(state, letter) -> GameState` is contracted only to RETURN the","+  updated state; implementations may mutate in place or return a fresh object.","+  Therefore callers MUST reassign (`state = apply_guess(state, letter)`) and","+  MUST NOT assume the input object is left unchanged. (binds source and tests)","+  [2026-06-12, task-001]","+"," ## Hygiene (binds the branch)"," "," - Never commit `__pycache__/` or `*.pyc`. Never create or write"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":50,"estimated_tokens_delta":50,"uuid":"c699047c-2aea-43d3-8c72-bb6148a4bad3","session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":162,"estimated_tokens_delta":112,"uuid":"37e6a5a1-0ab5-4ccd-8844-a8c0b0e4730b","session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a9"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_015f3oMfKz6P8DUamWCthPEa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":922,"cache_read_input_tokens":120557,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":922},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26931df1-8f61-42b8-a8d5-65221b0797a